    "• For the channel-mixing blocks (14, 15), µ k i and µ r i are initialized to (i s) 1-l L",
    "• w i (16), also known as \"time decay\", is initialized to -5 + 8 • (i d-1) 0.7+ 1.3l L-1.",
    "Intuitively, it is the discount factor applied to previous tokens over time.",
    "• u i (16), also known as \"bonus\", is set to 0.5 • (((i + 1) mod 3) -1) + log 0.3.",
    "It is the special weighting applied to the current token in equation 16."
  ],
